            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The problem is in `update_screen`, it invalidates all `msg_grid` rows that are used for displaying a message, when the screen is scrolled down back https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/22d397c233b12a94ba36052d9e626ed61e25d488/src/nvim/drawscreen.c#L458-L468  \r\nBut then, if redraw type is `UPD_NOT_VALID`, `msg_grid` rows from 0 to `p_ch` are used for compositing in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/22d397c233b12a94ba36052d9e626ed61e25d488/src/nvim/drawscreen.c#L535-L538  \r\nSo, any command that shows a scrolled message, and causes a `UPD_NOT_VALID` redraw should trigger the same bug. For example, `:split | echo \"\\n\"` command with `redrawdebug=invalid` set also triggers the bug.  \r\nHere's the fix I came up with:  \r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/drawscreen.c b/src/nvim/drawscreen.c\r\nindex 73dd584fb..608b7806d 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/drawscreen.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/drawscreen.c\r\n@@ -463,7 +463,7 @@ int update_screen(void)\r\n       // non-displayed part of msg_grid is considered invalid.\r\n       for (int i = 0; i < MIN(msg_scrollsize(), msg_grid.rows); i++) {\r\n         grid_clear_line(&msg_grid, msg_grid.line_offset[i],\r\n-                        msg_grid.cols, false);\r\n+                        msg_grid.cols, i < p_ch);\r\n       }\r\n     }\r\n     msg_grid.throttled = false;\r\n\r\n```",
